# ============================================================
# ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES — Thiru's Portfolio
# ------------------------------------------------------------
# 1. Copy this file to  frontend/.env.local  for local dev.
# 2. Add the same variables in your hosting provider's dashboard
#    for production (this file documents local dev only — no
#    hosting/deploy steps are covered here).
# 3. Every variable is explained in docs/ENVIRONMENT_SETUP.md.
#    Step-by-step key generation: docs/API_KEYS_SETUP.md
#    (or the per-service guides: docs/SUPABASE_SETUP.md,
#    docs/AI_SETUP.md, docs/EMAIL_SETUP.md).
#
# The site runs with ZERO of these set — every feature that
# needs a key checks for it and degrades gracefully (shows an
# "offline"/disabled state) rather than crashing. Add only what
# you want to enable.
#
# Values below are EXAMPLES, not real credentials — replace
# every one with your own before the feature will work.
# ============================================================

# ---------- Site ----------
# The public URL of the deployed site (no trailing slash). Used
# for SEO/sitemap/OG tags and as the AI provider's HTTP-Referer.
# Optional — falls back to http://localhost:3000.
NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL=http://localhost:3000

# ---------- Supabase (database + admin auth) ----------
# Powers: visitor ratings, Portfolio Insights, contact-message
# archive, newsletter signups, and the /admin CMS. Without these
# three, those features simply show an "offline" state.
# Get them from: Supabase dashboard → Project Settings → API.
# Full walkthrough: docs/SUPABASE_SETUP.md
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-ref.supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-supabase-anon-public-key
# Service role key — SERVER ONLY. Bypasses row-level security.
# Never expose in the browser, never prefix with NEXT_PUBLIC_.
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your-supabase-service-role-key

# ---------- Admin ----------
# The one email address allowed to sign in to /admin. Must match
# a user you create in Supabase Auth (Authentication → Users).
ADMIN_EMAIL=you@example.com

# ---------- AI Assistant ----------
# Tried in order — Gemini, then Groq, then OpenRouter — the
# first configured key wins for each request. All three are
# optional individually, but at least one is needed for the AI
# assistant / AI Workspace mode to answer questions.
# Full walkthrough: docs/AI_SETUP.md
GEMINI_API_KEY=your-gemini-api-key
GROQ_API_KEY=your-groq-api-key
OPENROUTER_API_KEY=your-openrouter-api-key

# ---------- Email (contact form) ----------
# SMTP is tried first; Web3Forms is the fallback if SMTP isn't
# configured or fails. Neither is required — messages still get
# archived to Supabase (if configured) either way.
# Full walkthrough: docs/EMAIL_SETUP.md
SMTP_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
SMTP_PORT=465
SMTP_USER=you@gmail.com
# Gmail: this MUST be a 16-character App Password, not your
# normal account password (requires 2-Step Verification).
SMTP_PASS=your-16-char-app-password
# Where contact-form messages are delivered. Optional — defaults
# to the `email` field in frontend/src/config/site.ts.
CONTACT_RECEIVER_EMAIL=you@gmail.com

# Fallback form provider — used only if SMTP_HOST/SMTP_USER/
# SMTP_PASS aren't all set.
WEB3FORMS_ACCESS_KEY=your-web3forms-access-key

# ---------- Analytics ----------
# Google Analytics 4 measurement ID. Optional — GA's script tags
# are only injected into the page when this is set.
NEXT_PUBLIC_GA_MEASUREMENT_ID=G-XXXXXXXXXX

# Minimum first-party page views before the public "Portfolio
# Insights" section shows real numbers (keeps early/low-traffic
# numbers private). Optional — defaults to 100 if unset.
NEXT_PUBLIC_INSIGHTS_MIN_VIEWS=100

# ------------------------------------------------------------
# NOT an environment variable: Vercel Analytics (the <Analytics />
# component already wired into the app) needs no configuration —
# it silently no-ops unless the app is actually running on Vercel.
#
# NOT an environment variable: GitHub stats (Activity section,
# Developer Dashboard) call the public, unauthenticated GitHub
# REST API — no token needed, nothing to configure.
# ------------------------------------------------------------
